xml.description:
Generate pure sine waves



The dual AD9833 module with a high bandwidth output opamp can generate up to 2 MHz pure sine waves with 0.015Hz resolution.


This module uses the CS1 and CS2 chip select outputs to control each of the Direct Digital Synthetis ICs, and the CS3 chip select is repurposed as a high speed clock output. The microcontroller can output up to 64MHz via CS3. It is set to 8MHz for this module.



Connections

The module has a 8*2 connector which plugs in directly into the seelab device

For this demo, the outputs are connected to A1 and A2, and two dynamic sliders are assigned to control the frequency of each DDS independently.



Output amplitude

Set to 3V via an opamp. This can be tweaked.
